Rules:
The game board has two sets of racing, horse and motor cycle.  There are 4 folds and 5 panels.  The inner rectangle, ringed in purple, denotes a horse racing track.  Three different courses are shown and each is laddered by blue lines, 1cm apart.  They are edged by a yellow border and contain 2 green and 2 red areas.  A cut out magazine picture has been labelled Lantham Castle and there is a paddock with tracks leading to each course.

The Motor Racing track rings the inner rectangle.  it contains 4 labelled bends and is situated in a patchwork of painted fields.  The start of the track is at the bottom ledft of the board and the finish  in the checkered area at the top right.  There are 4 main panels of rules dispersed on the board.  One side of the track is situated on a hill, the other contains the pits.  There is an area to place dice.

Rules placement: separate book
